282
00:13:15,044 --> 00:13:17,554
with one of these,
uh, Sudoku games.

283
00:13:17,630 --> 00:13:18,670
What, that
Japanese puzzle

284
00:13:18,756 --> 00:13:20,126
in which no numeral
can be repeated

285
00:13:20,216 --> 00:13:22,336
in a row, column, or box?

286
00:13:22,426 --> 00:13:23,886
That’s how it works?

287
00:13:23,969 --> 00:13:26,139
I was just drawing wangs
on the numbers.

288
00:13:26,222 --> 00:13:27,602
(panting)

289
00:13:27,681 --> 00:13:30,601
Moe, Moe, you got to hide us
from the Army.

290
00:13:30,684 --> 00:13:33,024
The Salvation Army?
You got it.

291
00:13:33,103 --> 00:13:35,443
Not that Army,
the one from <i>Stripes!</i>

292
00:13:35,523 --> 00:13:37,533
Okay.

293
00:13:39,485 --> 00:13:40,395
Thanks, Moe.

294
00:13:40,486 --> 00:13:41,986
How can I ever
repay you?

295
00:13:42,071 --> 00:13:44,491
Hey, some things mean
more to me than money.

296
00:13:45,616 --> 00:13:47,616
Like a whole lot
of money.

297
00:13:47,701 --> 00:13:49,831
Why did you just say
that sentence fragment?

298
00:13:49,912 --> 00:13:51,372
Uh, it, uh--
long story.

299
00:13:51,455 --> 00:13:52,535
(tires screeching)

300
00:13:57,878 --> 00:13:59,878
War game’s over, losers.

301
00:14:03,509 --> 00:14:05,759
Hey, they’s
using live ammo.

302
00:14:05,845 --> 00:14:06,795
Well, what have we got?

303
00:14:08,389 --> 00:14:10,099
Rise, my pretties.

304
00:14:10,182 --> 00:14:12,102
Find our enemies
and capture their image

305
00:14:12,184 --> 00:14:13,104
